'''eix''' from [[http://eix.berlios.de/ Berlios]] is a set of utilities for searching, diffing and updating a binary cache of your local portage-trees.

It is made to be more efficient and flexible than emerge's search functionality, comes with colorized output and helps you to more easily find the package information you need.

__TOC__

== Installation ==

To install eix run following command:

{{RootCmd|emerge -a eix}}

after the installation has finished, it is important to index all packages on the system.

== Updating the cache ==

Running following command will update the local eix cache and index all packages on the system.
{{RootCmd|eix-update}}

To spare out some typing work, run following command:
{{RootCmd|eix-sync}}

which is shorthand to run both commands sequentially:
{{RootCmd|emerge --sync}}
{{RootCmd|eix-update}}

=== Adding overlays to the cache ===

To search not only in the portage tree but all the overlays, add overlays to the cache
{{RootCmd|eix-remote update}}
{{RootCmd|eix-sync}}

== Searching the cache ==

Now that there are package entries in the cache you can search through them.

=== Finding more information about eix ===

For a quick overview about eix, you can run:

{{RootCmd|eix --help | more}}

For more detailed information, execute:

{{RootCmd|man eix}}

